The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Decision on venue soon
Mumbai: BCCI president Jagmohan Dalmiya said on Tuesday that the decision whether Kanpur would host the first Test between India and New Zealand from October 8-12 would be taken soon. The BCCI is still ascertaining the facts as to why the Test match cannot be held in Kanpur as planned and Im sure we will be able to decide on this issue soon, Dalmiya, who is here to attend Wednesdays marketing committee meeting, said. Kasturirangan resigns Dalmiya also confirmed that G. Kasturirangan, the chairman of grounds and pitches committee of the BCCI, had resigned on Monday on health grounds. (PTI)  Copyright 
